title: Dear Arthur, Love John - Radio Drama
description:
1 x 45 mins

Dad's Army was a fixture on British TV screens in the early to mid 1970s, telling the tale of the fictional Walmington on Sea Home Guard, a group of those too young, too old or too devious to avoid serving in the armed forces. Such is the show's popularity, that it is still regularly repeated today.

Roy Smiles play looks at the creation of the series and the sometimes difficult off-screen relationships. A beautifully crafted piece
